      "text": "Scanning means searching a wide area with your eyes to find some particular thing,",
      "start": 180.94,
      "end": 185.98,
      "words": [
        "Scanning",
        "means",
        "searching",
        "a",
        "wide",
        "area",
        "with",
        "your",
        "eyes",
        "to",
        "find",
        "some",
        "particular",
        "thing"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "in this case,",
      "start": 186.38,
      "end": 187.02,
      "words": [
        "in",
        "this",
        "case"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "edible plants and herbs.",
      "start": 187.1,
      "end": 188.78,
      "words": [
        "edible",
        "plants",
        "and",
        "herbs"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And of course,",
      "start": 189.1,
      "end": 189.82,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "of",
        "course"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Roshana only eats plants that she can positively identify,",
      "start": 189.98,
      "end": 193.26,
      "words": [
        "Roshana",
        "only",
        "eats",
        "plants",
        "that",
        "she",
        "can",
        "positively",
        "identify"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "plants that she knows",
      "start": 193.58,
      "end": 194.62,
      "words": [
        "plants",
        "that",
        "she",
        "knows"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "110% are safe to eat.",
      "start": 195.34,
      "end": 197.1,
      "words": [
        "110",
        "are",
        "safe",
        "to",
        "eat"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Here the idiom",
      "start": 197.42,
      "end": 198.38,
      "words": [
        "Here",
        "the",
        "idiom"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "110% means Roshana is completely sure,",
      "start": 199.18,
      "end": 201.58,
      "words": [
        "110",
        "means",
        "Roshana",
        "is",
        "completely",
        "sure"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "she has no doubt.",
      "start": 201.66,
      "end": 202.94,
      "words": [
        "she",
        "has",
        "no",
        "doubt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And that's important as the consequences of eating poisonous plants are serious– sickness or even death.",
      "start": 203.42,
      "end": 209.5,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "that's",
        "important",
        "as",
        "the",
        "consequences",
        "of",
        "eating",
        "poisonous",
        "plants",
        "are",
        "serious",
        "sickness",
        "or",
        "even",
        "death"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Our second female forager,",
      "start": 209.996,
      "end": 211.596,
      "words": [
        "Our",
        "second",
        "female",
        "forager"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Emily Smith,",
      "start": 211.756,
      "end": 212.476,
      "words": [
        "Emily",
        "Smith"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "moved to rural Japan to work on a project cataloguing and collecting wild mushrooms.",
      "start": 212.956,
      "end": 218.956,
      "words": [
        "moved",
        "to",
        "rural",
        "Japan",
        "to",
        "work",
        "on",
        "a",
        "project",
        "cataloguing",
        "and",
        "collecting",
        "wild",
        "mushrooms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "With around 5,",
      "start": 219.196,
      "end": 220.236,
      "words": [
        "With",
        "around",
        "5"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "000 varieties,",
      "start": 220.236,
      "end": 221.756,
      "words": [
        "000",
        "varieties"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "300 of which are edible,",
      "start": 222.156,
      "end": 224.076,
      "words": [
        "300",
        "of",
        "which",
        "are",
        "edible"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "mushrooms are an important part of traditional Japanese cooking.",
      "start": 224.476,
      "end": 228.316,
      "words": [
        "mushrooms",
        "are",
        "an",
        "important",
        "part",
        "of",
        "traditional",
        "Japanese",
        "cooking"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "But with names like death cap and a reputation for being poisonous,",
      "start": 228.876,
      "end": 233.596,
      "words": [
        "But",
        "with",
        "names",
        "like",
        "death",
        "cap",
        "and",
        "a",
        "reputation",
        "for",
        "being",
        "poisonous"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "mushrooms are what many wild foragers worry about the most.",
      "start": 233.916,
      "end": 238.076,
      "words": [
        "mushrooms",
        "are",
        "what",
        "many",
        "wild",
        "foragers",
        "worry",
        "about",
        "the",
        "most"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Emily discussed these worries with BBC World Service programme The Conversation.",
      "start": 238.636,
      "end": 243.596,
      "words": [
        "Emily",
        "discussed",
        "these",
        "worries",
        "with",
        "BBC",
        "World",
        "Service",
        "programme",
        "The",
        "Conversation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "That stigma is a",
      "start": 243.98,
      "end": 245.58,
      "words": [
        "That",
        "stigma",
        "is",
        "a"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "bit misplaced,",
      "start": 246.38,
      "end": 247.02,
      "words": [
        "bit",
        "misplaced"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "I think,",
      "start": 247.02,
      "end": 247.34,
      "words": [
        "I",
        "think"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "because plants can be just as dangerous,",
      "start": 247.34,
      "end": 249.26,
      "words": [
        "because",
        "plants",
        "can",
        "be",
        "just",
        "as",
        "dangerous"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "if not more dangerous,",
      "start": 249.26,
      "end": 250.3,
      "words": [
        "if",
        "not",
        "more",
        "dangerous"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "than mushrooms.",
      "start": 250.3,
      "end": 250.94,
      "words": [
        "than",
        "mushrooms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And I think that mushrooms have been much",
      "start": 250.94,
      "end": 252.14,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "I",
        "think",
        "that",
        "mushrooms",
        "have",
        "been",
        "much"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "maligned.",
      "start": 253.1,
      "end": 253.74,
      "words": [
        "maligned"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "I mean,",
      "start": 254.3,
      "end": 254.62,
      "words": [
        "I",
        "mean"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "you've got to exercise caution,",
      "start": 254.78,
      "end": 255.98,
      "words": [
        "you've",
        "got",
        "to",
        "exercise",
        "caution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "as Roshana said,",
      "start": 255.98,
      "end": 256.94,
      "words": [
        "as",
        "Roshana",
        "said"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "in anything that you pick.",
      "start": 257.26,
      "end": 259.02,
      "words": [
        "in",
        "anything",
        "that",
        "you",
        "pick"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "You need to know what it is before you consume it.",
      "start": 259.42,
      "end": 261.18,
      "words": [
        "You",
        "need",
        "to",
        "know",
        "what",
        "it",
        "is",
        "before",
        "you",
        "consume",
        "it"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "If in doubt,",
      "start": 261.26,
      "end": 261.98,
      "words": [
        "If",
        "in",
        "doubt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "throw it out is a very good phrase to say.",
      "start": 261.98,
      "end": 264.7,
      "words": [
        "throw",
        "it",
        "out",
        "is",
        "a",
        "very",
        "good",
        "phrase",
        "to",
        "say"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Emily thinks there's a stigma around mushrooms.",
      "start": 265.196,
      "end": 268.156,
      "words": [
        "Emily",
        "thinks",
        "there's",
        "a",
        "stigma",
        "around",
        "mushrooms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "A stigma is a negative belief about something which is not necessarily true or fair.",
      "start": 268.396,
      "end": 273.756,
      "words": [
        "A",
        "stigma",
        "is",
        "a",
        "negative",
        "belief",
        "about",
        "something",
        "which",
        "is",
        "not",
        "necessarily",
        "true",
        "or",
        "fair"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "In fact,",
      "start": 274.156,
      "end": 274.636,
      "words": [
        "In",
        "fact"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "many plants are just as poisonous as mushrooms.",
      "start": 274.716,
      "end": 277.356,
      "words": [
        "many",
        "plants",
        "are",
        "just",
        "as",
        "poisonous",
        "as",
        "mushrooms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "The main thing is to exercise caution to act with care and attention so as to avoid possible dangers.",
      "start": 277.676,
      "end": 284.716,
      "words": [
        "The",
        "main",
        "thing",
        "is",
        "to",
        "exercise",
        "caution",
        "to",
        "act",
        "with",
        "care",
        "and",
        "attention",
        "so",
        "as",
        "to",
        "avoid",
        "possible",
        "dangers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "In other words,",
      "start": 285.036,
      "end": 285.676,
      "words": [
        "In",
        "other",
        "words"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "to be careful.",
      "start": 285.836,
      "end": 286.796,
      "words": [
        "to",
        "be",
        "careful"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And the best way of doing that is learning the difference between what's safe to eat and what's not.",
      "start": 287.116,
      "end": 291.836,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "the",
        "best",
        "way",
        "of",
        "doing",
        "that",
        "is",
        "learning",
        "the",
        "difference",
        "between",
        "what's",
        "safe",
        "to",
        "eat",
        "and",
        "what's",
        "not"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Speaking of which,",
      "start": 292.236,
      "end": 293.116,
      "words": [
        "Speaking",
        "of",
        "which"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "what was the answer to your question,",
      "start": 293.196,
      "end": 294.636,
      "words": [
        "what",
        "was",
        "the",
        "answer",
        "to",
        "your",
        "question"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Beth?",
      "start": 294.636,
      "end": 294.876,
      "words": [
        "Beth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Ah,",
      "start": 295.276,
      "end": 295.836,
      "words": [
        "Ah"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "I asked you what colour are death cap mushrooms.",
      "start": 295.836,
      "end": 298.876,
      "words": [
        "I",
        "asked",
        "you",
        "what",
        "colour",
        "are",
        "death",
        "cap",
        "mushrooms"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "You said red,",
      "start": 299.276,
      "end": 300.236,
      "words": [
        "You",
        "said",
        "red"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "which I also thought was the answer,",
      "start": 300.556,
      "end": 302.316,
      "words": [
        "which",
        "I",
        "also",
        "thought",
        "was",
        "the",
        "answer"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "but actually they are white.",
      "start": 302.396,
      "end": 304.156,
      "words": [
        "but",
        "actually",
        "they",
        "are",
        "white"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Right,",
      "start": 304.684,
      "end": 305.004,
      "words": [
        "Right"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "it's time to recap the vocabulary we've learnt about foraging.",
      "start": 305.004,
      "end": 309.084,
      "words": [
        "it's",
        "time",
        "to",
        "recap",
        "the",
        "vocabulary",
        "we've",
        "learnt",
        "about",
        "foraging"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Right.",
      "start": 304.716,
      "end": 304.956,
      "words": [
        "Right"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Starting with horticulturalist– a person who studies or grows plants.",
      "start": 309.324,
      "end": 314.124,
      "words": [
        "Starting",
        "with",
        "horticulturalist",
        "a",
        "person",
        "who",
        "studies",
        "or",
        "grows",
        "plants"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "If you have a deep knowledge of a subject,",
      "start": 314.524,
      "end": 316.844,
      "words": [
        "If",
        "you",
        "have",
        "a",
        "deep",
        "knowledge",
        "of",
        "a",
        "subject"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "you have a thorough understanding of it gained from experience and study.",
      "start": 317.004,
      "end": 321.164,
      "words": [
        "you",
        "have",
        "a",
        "thorough",
        "understanding",
        "of",
        "it",
        "gained",
        "from",
        "experience",
        "and",
        "study"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Scanning involves searching a wide area with your eyes to find some particular thing.",
      "start": 321.484,
      "end": 326.924,
      "words": [
        "Scanning",
        "involves",
        "searching",
        "a",
        "wide",
        "area",
        "with",
        "your",
        "eyes",
        "to",
        "find",
        "some",
        "particular",
        "thing"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "If you're 110% sure about something,",
      "start": 327.404,
      "end": 330.364,
      "words": [
        "If",
        "you're",
        "110",
        "sure",
        "about",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "you're absolutely certain– you have no doubt.",
      "start": 330.604,
      "end": 333.164,
      "words": [
        "you're",
        "absolutely",
        "certain",
        "you",
        "have",
        "no",
        "doubt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "A stigma is an unfair negative belief about something.",
      "start": 333.1,
      "end": 337.1,
      "words": [
        "A",
        "stigma",
        "is",
        "an",
        "unfair",
        "negative",
        "belief",
        "about",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And finally,",
      "start": 337.5,
      "end": 338.38,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "finally"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "to exercise caution is a more formal way of saying to be careful something you should definitely remember if you go wild foraging yourself.",
      "start": 338.46,
      "end": 346.22,
      "words": [
        "to",
        "exercise",
        "caution",
        "is",
        "a",
        "more",
        "formal",
        "way",
        "of",
        "saying",
        "to",
        "be",
        "careful",
        "something",
        "you",
        "should",
        "definitely",
        "remember",
        "if",
        "you",
        "go",
        "wild",
        "foraging",
        "yourself"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Once again,",
      "start": 346.86,
      "end": 347.5,
      "words": [
        "Once",
        "again"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "our six minutes are up.",
